        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 2:13PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 212 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Society Hill, or 11 miles northwest of Hurtsboro, moving east at 45
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tuskegee, Hurtsboro, Franklin, Liverpool, Russell County Sports
Complex, Uchee, Seale, Lake Tuskegee, Davisville, Society Hill,
Warriorstand, Uphapee Creek, Creek Stand, Rutherford, Hatchechubbe,
Marvyn, Moton Field Municipal Airport, and Parkmanville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for
southeastern and east central Alabama.</instruction>
